==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Martian
<hw>Mar"tian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Martius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Mars, the Roman god
of war, or to the planet bearing his name; martial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Martian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Martian
<hw>Mar"tian</hw>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>An inhabitant of the planet
Mars; -- fictional or hypothetical.</def> <rj><au>Du
Maurier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In science fiction, it has often been postulated that
there are intelligent creatures living on Mars, but no strong evidence
of any form of life on Mars has been observed up to the end of
1998.</note></p>

<p><ent>Martin</ent>⟦br⟧
